refactor: optimize lazy.nvim config for better performance and maintainability
# Please enter the commit message for your changes. Lines starting
# with '#' will be ignored, and an empty message aborts the commit.

- Add shared utils module to reduce code duplication
- Switch plugins to lazy-load on keys instead of events (fzf, comment, surround)
- Simplify init.lua and remove redundant performance configs
- Extract LSP keymaps and highlight setup to reusable functions
- Consolidate plugin configs using opts pattern
- Reduce total config lines by ~37% while maintaining functionality

